e" title="Orange" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/orange">Orange</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">or-ange </span><p>One of the best-known citrus fruits, oranges aren't necessarily orange - some varieties are…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 whole cloves">6 whole <a href="/glossary/clove" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">cloves</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-259651" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/clove"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/cloves.jpg?itok=Nqd1UYuO" width="100" height="100" alt="Cloves" title="Cloves can be used whole or ground to impart a strong sweet but spicy and peppery flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/clove">Clove</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">klo-ve</span><p>The dry, unopened flower bud of the tropical myrtle tree family used to flavour a wide variety…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 whole allspice">6 whole allspice</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 cinnamon sticks">2 cinnamon sticks</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="&frac14; nutmeg, freshly grated">&frac14; <a href="/glossary/nutmeg" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">nutmeg</a>, freshly grated<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-6458441" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/nutmeg"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/03/nutmeg_700.jpg?itok=tuPKYNYY" width="100" height="100" alt="Nutmeg" title="Nutmeg" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/nutmeg">Nutmeg</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">nut-meg</span><p><span style="line-height:107%">One of the most useful of spices for both sweet and savoury</span>…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="small piece ginger, sliced">small piece <a href="/glossary/ginger" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">ginger</a>, sliced<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-253916" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/ginger"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/ginger.jpg?itok=Cbx3HRcX" width="100" height="100" alt="Ginger" title="Ginger has bulbous little joints, from which grow small, knobbly bumps, and its skin is light brown with a slight silvery quality" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/ginger">Ginger</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">jin-jer</span><p>Mainly grown in Jamaica, Africa, India, China and Australia, ginger is the root of the plant. It…</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Put all the ingredients into a saucepan with 1 litre water and bring slowly to a simmer, making sure all the sugar has been completely dissolved. Turn down the heat and simmer for 20 mins. Leave to cool, then strain through a very fine sieve.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Sterilise your bottles by washing them in hot soapy water, rinsing well, then drying them in a warm oven. Meanwhile, rewarm the syrup until just hot, then pour into the bottles while still hot and seal.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Before giving away, add labels with serving instructions: <i>Heat 400ml syrup with 750ml red wine or cider and some slices of orange or apple. Syrup will keep in a cool, dark place for up to 3 months.</i></p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1288569600" class="text-style-alt">November 2010</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div><div class="recipe__tips"><div class="field field-name-field-bbcgf-tips field-type-entityreference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><div class="view view-recipe-views view-id-recipe_views view-display-id-tips view-dom-id-06414330010a38bbfeebe5842734717f"><div class="view-content"><div class="carousel-tips__wrapper carousel"><div class="flexslider carousel-tips__elements" data-type="carousel-tips"><ul class="slides carousel-tips__slides"><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">Presenting your gift</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">Make up a kit as a gift by tying some
cinnamon sticks to the neck of the bottle
with ribbon, and accompanying it with
a good red wine. You can buy nice
preserving bottles from lakeland.co.uk.</div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-96178" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/user-collections/my-colelction-image/2015/12/recipe-image-legacy-id--459707_12.jpg?itok=KsOBlW0A" width="324" height="294" alt="Ginger beer &amp; tangerine glazed ham" title="Ginger beer &amp; tangerine glazed ham" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/864635/ginger-beer-and-tangerine-glazed-ham"> Ginger beer &amp; tangerine glazed ham </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-text"><div class="fivestar-static-form-item"><div class="form-item form-type-item"><div class="field-main"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">4.44</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div><div class="description"><p class="fivestar-summary fivestar-summary-">(25 <span class="rating-text"> ratings</span>)</p></div></div></div></div></div> </article></li><li class=""><article id="node-94977" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><