es</h2><ul class="pager unstyled horizontal-elements"><li class="pager-current first">1</li><li class="pager-item"><a title="Go to page 2" href="/recipes/851643/mulling-syrup?page=1#c">2</a></li><li class="pager-item"><a title="Go to page 3" href="/recipes/851643/mulling-syrup?page=2#c">3</a></li><li class="pager-item"><a title="Go to page 4" href="/recipes/851643/mulling-syrup?page=3#c">4</a></li><li class="pager-next bg-turquoise-safe last"><a title="Go to next page" href="/recipes/851643/mulling-syrup?page=1#c">next ›</a></li></ul></div></div><div id="fragment-question" class="section-comments__single-tab-content"><div class="view view-comment-views-comment-ajax view-id-comment_views_comment_ajax view-display-id-quest_page view-dom-id-bca4ec1c344259eb5426f8666d9df28f"><div class="view-content"><div><div id="comment-wrapper-894651"><a id="comment-894651"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">ldupuy</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 22nd Dec, 2015</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Hello,
After reading some comment complaining about the consistency & as per other syrup recipes (including on this site), I was wondering if doubling the amount of sugar (to balance the amount of liquid) would be a good idea?
